  {
    "key": "8fe5d46f-0003-480e-a7f3-a6789ff9f3d6",
    "name": "Admission criteria",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Admission criteria",
    "content": "<p>Applicants, in order to be considered for admission should have a Greek Secondary School Diploma / ‘Apolyterion of Lykeio’ or equivalent (e.g., International Baccalaureate, European Baccalaureate, etc.) with a grade 10 or above. This requirement is in line with the Greek government’s minimum standard for access to higher education.</p>\n<p>High school leaving certificates issued by vocational Lyceums, such as TEE or EPAL and foreign certificates which are equivalent to the Greek Lyceum certificate (e.g. International Baccalaureate, European Baccalaureate, etc.) are also accepted.</p>\n<p>Non-native Greek speakers, may be admitted to the programme on demonstrating that:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>a) They hold a qualification recognised by QMU for admission to undergraduate programmes, as documented in the University Admissions Regulations.</li>\n<li>b) They hold a certificate of attainment in Greek at Level D</li>\n</ol>\n<p> (<a href=\"http://www.greeklanguage.gr/greekLang/certification/index.html\" title=\"Greek language certification\">http://www.greeklanguage.gr/greekLang/certification/index.html</a>)</p>"
  }
]]]></Value>
